Community Police Forum chair Cathy Cronje says there was a spike in violence, with murders over the weekend. CAPE TOWN - The Community Police Forum (CPF) in Ocean View says poorly resourced police are buckling under crime in the area.CPF chairperson Cathy Cronje says there was a spike in violence, with murders over the weekend. I think the police try their best with the little resources that they have. I think they re completely under resource and they need to fill the vacant positions so we can start taking control. The body of 14-year-old Cameron Britz was discovered on Sunday, a day after she was reported missing.One person has been arrested in connection with her killing.An 18-year-old girl was also shot and killed at the weekend.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)